# Comparison of Approaches

| Approach           | Time Complexity   | Space | Suitable For                |
| ------------------ | ----------------- | ----- | --------------------------- |
| Brute Force        | O(k × n)          | O(1)  | Small inputs                |
| Max Heap           | O(k log n)        | O(n)  | Medium inputs               |
| Binary Search + AP | O(n log MaxValue) | O(1)  | Large constraints (Optimal) |

---

# Key Interview Points

* Greedy idea: always sell the highest-priced ticket first.
* Brute force repeatedly searches for the maximum.
* Max heap reduces maximum retrieval from **O(n)** to **O(log n)**.
* The optimal solution avoids simulating each sale by:

  * Binary searching the cutoff (selling) level.
  * Using the arithmetic progression formula to compute profit in bulk.
* This makes it efficient even when `k` is very large.

